name: seq
longDescription: Print numbers from FIRST to LAST, in steps of INCREMENT.

options.name: equal-width
options.description: Print all numbers with the same width, by padding with leading zeros.  FIRST, STEP, and LAST should all use a fixed point decimal representation.  (To have other kinds of padding, use ‘--format’).

options.name: format
options.description: Print all numbers using FORMAT.  FORMAT must contain exactly one of the ‘printf’-style floating point conversion specifications ‘%a’, ‘%e’, ‘%f’, ‘%g’, ‘%A’, ‘%E’, ‘%F’, ‘%G’.  The ‘%’ may be followed by zero or more flags taken from the set ‘-+#0 '’, then an optional width containing one or more digits, then an optional precision consisting of a ‘.’ followed by zero or more digits.  FORMAT may also contain any number of ‘%%’ conversion specifications.  All conversion specifications have the same meaning as with ‘printf’.

options.name: separator
options.description: Separate numbers with STRING; default is a newline.  The output always terminates with a newline.
